Commentary: OUT! Caught down the leg side! Wow! What a start! Dean Elgar is out of here on the first ball of the Boxing Day Test. Just a feather down the leg side but Anderson and England won't care. 150th Test for Jimmy and what a start for England. A gentle length ball down the leg side. Elgar looks to tickle it fine off his pads but he can only get a feather behind. Buttler behind the wickets makes no mistake and England are off to a perfect start and well, South Africa, not sure what to say. Such a soft dismissal, this one.
Good length ball outside off, Hamza makes a leave.

Edgy FOUR! Hamza is off the mark! Anderson goes full just outside off, Hamza comes forward and defends. The ball takes the thick outside edge and goes to the third man fence. First boundary off the game! Not the way the hosts would have wanted it to come but they will take it.
On the pads, Hamza works it fine down the leg side for a single.
Good length ball around off, Markram defends it with a straight bat.
In the channel outside off, Markram makes a leave. End of the first over and a successful one too.
Archer starts with a fuller ball on middle, Zubayr flicks it to deep square leg and changes end.

FOUR! Shot! A fuller ball around off, Markram just comes forward and pushes it defensively. The mid on fielder dives to his left to stop but fails to do so. It races to the fence and Markram is off the mark in a nice fashion.
Around off on a length, it is defended.
Beaten! Beauty from Broad. A good length ball outside off, shaping away nicely. Markram plays at it but the ball goes away beating the outside edge and to the keeper.
Outside off, Markram makes a leave.
Fuller and outside off, Markram is not into driving as he lets it go to the keeper.
Good length ball around off and middle, it is angled in. Hamza looks to defend but gets an inside edge on the thigh pads.
Good length ball way outside off, Hamza lets it be.
Fuller but very wide outside off, Hamza shows no interest as he shoulders arms.
Make that third leave in a row as Zubayr allows this good length ball outside off go to Buttler behind the wicket.
Around off on a length, Hamza defends it out.
Fullish but once again outside off, Hamza shoulders arms once again. Anderson needs to get closer to off pole and make the batter play.
Fuller and on off, Markram tucks it towards mid-wicket and takes a single.
Nicely punched! A slightly fullish ball, Hamza strokes it past mid on and picks a couple of easy runs before the mid on fielder can get to the ball.
Just behind good length but outside off, Hamza allows it to go to the keeper.
Good length around off, Hamza works it towards mid on and thinks of a run but they decide against it as the ball went to the mid on fielder quickly.
Slightly fuller but once again way outside off, it is Broad this time. Hamza lets it be.
Good length which is again outside off and Hamza has no problem letting this go to the keeper.
FOUR! Driven handsomely! Full and wide outside off, inviting the batter to go for the drive. Markram accepts it and creams the drive through covers. It races to the sweeper cover fence in a jiffy.

FOUR! Make that two in a row! They say, slash and slash hard. That's what Markram does. A good length ball outside off, he throws the kitchen sink at it. The ball takes the thick outside edge and flies over the leaping second slip fielder.

Three more! This time through the covers. Slightly short and outside off, Markram rides the bounce and punches it nicely. Denly hares after the ball and makes a sliding stop just before the fence. A single saved.
Outside off this time, Hamza lets it go to the keeper.
In the channel outside off, it is left alone.
Hamza makes third consecutive leave to end a good over for South Africa. 11 from the over, all coming from Markram's bat though.
Broad starts the fresh over by bowling a fuller ball around off, Markram blocks it away.
Good length ball around off, Markram makes a solid defensive shot off the back foot.
Outside off, Markram is not interested as he shoulders arms to this one.
Landed around off, it is defended.
Good length ball outside off, left alone.
Good length ball this one which is aimed into the batter. Markram in the defense gets squared up. The ball takes the outer half and goes to the gully fielder on the bounce.

Confusion but safe... A good length ball around off, Hamza defends it towards point. Markram quickly takes off for the single but Hamza sends him back. Markram is almost halfway in the middle. Denly gets to the ball and fires the throw at the non-striker's end. He misses his shy but Markram had returned well in time.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
In the channel outside off, Hamza lets it be.
Good length ball on off, Hamza stays on the back foot and punches it straight to gully.
Goes full on off, Hamza drives it straight to short extra cover.
Full and on off again, Hamza pushes it right of the short extra cover fielder and takes a quick single.
Good length ball on middle, Hamza works it towards deep square leg. Before the fine leg fielder can come around to pick the ball up, the batters get a couple of runs.
Sprays down the leg side on a length. Hamza lets it go to the keeper.
Bends his back and bowls it short but once again the line is down the leg side which will not trouble Hamza. He ducks under it.
Good length ball on middle, Hamza works it wide of the mid on fielder and takes a single.
Landed on middle, it is defended towards mid-wicket.
Fuller ball just outside off, Markram has his sticks covered and lets it be.
Good stop! A full ball down the leg side, Hamza looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. Buttler behind the wicket dives to his left and stops the ball.
Fuller and just outside off, defended towards mid off.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Good length ball, this one comes back in nicely. Hamza does well to get his bat down in time to defend.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Good length ball around off, Hamza pushes it towards point.
FOUR! What a welcome for him into the attack.  A fuller ball around off, Markram leans forwards and lofts this over the cover region beautifully. A top shot.
Beaten! Curran gets his line and length right and bowls it just outside off, Markram pokes to get beaten.
Edged but just short! A good length ball, closer to the off pole, Markram once again pokes. This time the ball catches the outside edge. It goes to the first slip on the bounce.

OUT! Caught at mid-wicket. Another soft dismissal. Curran with the knack of picking wickets has struck in the very first over. A good length ball on middle, Markram looks to work it on the leg side. However, he ends up chipping it towards mid-wicket. Bairstow there gets low down and pouches the catch inches above the turf. The good-looking stand is broken.
Fuller ball on off, it is defended.
Full and on middle, flicked to mid-wicket.

Brave leave! A brilliant start for Archer though! This wasn't too far away from the top of off. Good line and length. This one pitches just outside off and then comes back in. Hamza lets it go to the keeper.
Good length ball angled into the right-hander, Hamza defends but the ball takes inside edge and hits on the body.
Wide outside off this one, Hamza lets it be.
Big bouncer on middle, Hamza easily ducks under it.
Looses his line and sprays this one down the leg side. Buttler moves to his left and does well to pouch the ball on that side.
FOUR! Flicked nicely! A full ball on middle, Hamza easily flicks it towards deep square leg. The ball races to the fence quickly. Poor ball by Archer to finish the over.
Good length ball shaping away from the right-hander. Faf lets it go to the keeper.
Back of a length ball on middle, du Plessis hops and blocks it on the leg side.

Brilliant ball from Curran again. Another ball that lands on middle and off and it shapes just a hint. Faf has to play at it and as he does that, he is squared up. The ball takes the thick outside edge and goes to the gully fielder.
On off, it is blocked.
This time Curran bowls it full on middle, Faf flicks it nicely but finds mid-wicket.
Beaten! Peach to finish the over! Superb delivery from the left-armer. Lands it on a good length and around off. Once again makes it shape away from the poke of Faf. Lucky not to edge that one.

Quick single! A good length ball around off and middle, Hamza works it towards mid on and takes off for a single. Broad gets there quickly, picks the ball and has a shy at the striker's end. He though misses but du Plessis had made his ground anyway.
Outside off, left alone.
Low full toss outside off, du Plessis reaches out and squeezes it through covers. He is off and running with a couple of runs.

Just short of Bairstow at short leg. A back of a length ball on middle, du Plessis hops to defend but the ball hits the upper part of the bat and lobs right of Bairstow at short leg. Bairstow dives to his right to catch but the ball ends up just short.
Outside off, it is left alone.
On the length around off, du Plessis defends it out.
Curran starts the fresh over post the drinks break by spraying on the pads. Hamza flicks it to fine leg for a run and crosses over.
Slightly shortish and outside off, du Plessis allows it go to the keeper.
Fuller ball around off, du Plessis keeps it out.
WIDE! A bouncer this time but it is way over du Plessis. Called wide.
Good length ball just outside off, du Plessis taps it towards cover off the back foot.
Full and off, defended back to the bowler.
Full and on off again, du Plessis is solid in his drive towards mid off.
Archer bowls it on a good length on off, Hamza stands tall and defends it off the back foot.
Outside off, Hamza offers no shot to this one.

FOUR! Don't bother running that was four the moment it left the bat. Poor ball from Archer. Short and wide outside off. Hamza is quick to pounce on it and punches it right off the meat through point for a boundary.

A bit of indecisiveness from Hamza! Good length ball just around off. It is shaping away from Hamza. He initially looks to defend but then sees that it is going away from his off pole so he retracts on his decision.
Bowls a bouncer outside off, Hamza does well to duck under it.
BEATEN! On a good length and just outside off, Hamza looks to defend but misses it.
On a good length and outside off, du Plessis plays it to covers off the back foot.
Good length delivery on middle, the skipper keeps it out.
On a good length on off, du Plessis plays it to covers.
Good length delivery on off, Faf offers a solid defense on this one.
On a good length around off, du Plessis blocks it off the back foot.
Outside off, du Plessis leaves it alone.
FOUR! Overpitched and punished! Full and wide outside off, Hamza leans into the drive and slams it through covers.

FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries for Hamza. A good length ball around off, Hamza this time strokes this through mid off. Brilliant followthrough on this shot. Held the pose for the cameras there. 50 up for South Africa.
On middle, Hamza nudges it to fine leg and crosses for a run.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.

EDGY FOUR! Tight line this from Archer. He lands it on a shortish length around off, du Plessis hops and looks to defend but the ball takes the thick outside edge and goes past the diving Ben Stokes. However, it is wide of him and ends up going to the fence. Four for du Plessis and South Africa but Archer won't mind this.
Fuller and off, driven wide of the cover fielder for a single. 14 from the over.
Good length ball just outside off, Faf punches it through point for a couple of runs.
Good length delivery on middle, du Plessis blocks it off the back foot.
Full and on middle, flicked to mid-wicket.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Landed around middle, du Plessis works it towards mid-wicket.
Fuller ball way outside off, Faf lets it go to the keeper.
Anderson starts the fresh spell but spraying down the leg side on the first ball. Hamza flicks but makes no connection.
Full delivery on off, Hamza drives it to mid off.
On a good length on middle, Hamza defends it off the back foot.
Length delivery on middle, Hamza flicks it through square leg for a single.
On a good length on off, the skipper defends it out.
Outside off, Faf leaves it alone.
Full delivery on middle, Hamza drives it towards mid on where Anderson dives and does well to stop it.
Outside off, Hamza does not bother to play at that.
Again outside off, Hamza leaves it alone.
BEATEN! On a good length and outside off, Hamza looks to defend but misses it.
BEATEN! On a good length and outside off, Hamza looks to defend again but misses it.
On a length on off, Hamza taps it to point.
Full delivery on off, du Plessis plays it to covers.
On a length on middle, Faf flicks it towards mid-wicket for a run.
Good length delivery on off, Hamza defends it to mid off.
Full delivery on off, Hamza drives it to mid off.
Outside off, Hamza shoulders arms to this one.
Length delivery on leg, Hamza flicks it towards fine leg. The batsmen cross ends.
On a good length on off, Hamza blocks it well.
Good length delivery on middle, Hamza defends it back towards the bowler.
On a good length on off, Hamza keeps it out.
NO BALL! Broad oversteps! Length delivery on middle, Hamza flicks it through mid-wicket. Bairstow chases it and does well to stop it before the ropes. The batsmen get two runs.
Outside off, Hamza does not bother to play at that.
FOUR! Magnificently timed! Slightly overpitched and Hamza pounces on it nicely. Fuller and outside off, Hamza leans into the drive and creams it through covers. Poses for the cameras there.

OUT! Caught next ball. Broad has broken the stand. A good length ball outside off, shaping away from the right-hander.  Hamza can easily leave these but he pokes at it. The ball takes the outside edge and goes to Stokes at second slip. He pouches it with both hands and sends Hamza packing. Broad and England celebrate. Timely wicket for the visitors.
Fuller ball on off, pushed to point.

EDGED AND FOUR! Good length ball around off, it moves away from Faf. He looks to defend it with soft hands but gets an outside edge which goes wide of the man at slip and races away to the fence. Had he played that with hard hands then it might have carried to the fielder there.
On a good length on off, du Plessis defends it to covers.
Outside off, du Plessis offers a calm leave on this one.
Good length delivery on off, Faf blocks it off the front foot.
Outside off, du Plessis lets it go.
On a good length on off, van der Dussen defends it back towards the bowler.
Full delivery on off, van der Dussen drives it to mid off.
On a good length on off, van der Dussen blocks it off the front foot.
Outside off, Rassie offers no shot to this one.
Again outside off, van der Dussen lets it go.
FOUR! Excellent shot. Full delivery on middle, van der Dussen flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary.

OHH! Just a tad too high maybe. Excellent ball this from Jofra. Steams in and bowls a inswinging length ball around off. Faf looks to defend but the ball comes in viciously and hits him on the thigh pad of his back leg. There is a huge appeal from the English players but the umpire is unmoved. Joe Root has a brief thought about a review but opts against it. Good decision from Joe as Hawk Eye later on shows that the ball was going well over the stumps.
Another very good inswinging ball. This time Faf gets a bit of bat on it. Length ball, jagging back in from off. Du Plessis looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Archer misses his line and sprays one down the leg side. Faf is not interested in playing that.
Good stop. On the pads, du Plessis flicks it but Bairstow at short leg shows good reflex and saves runs for his side.
Back of a length on off, du Plessis defends it off his back foot.
Bouncer to end the over. It is around the body, du Plessis sits under it.
Outside off, van der Dussen offers no shot to this one.
On a good length on off, van der Dussen defends it off the back foot.
Good length delivery on middle, Rassie blocks it off the back foot.
Full delivery on middle, Rassie drives it to mid on.
On a good length on middle, van der Dussen defends it off the back foot.
Length ball on the stumps, van der Dussen defends it with a straight bat to negotiate the final over of the session without any casualty. That will be Lunch on Day 1!
Archer starts with a ball on the pads of du Plessis. He clips it towards deep square leg for a couple of runs.
FOUR! This time clipped through mid-wicket. Another fuller length ball around off and middle, du Plessis uses his wrists and whips it to the deep mid-wicket fence.
Around off, it is defended.
FOUR! Second boundary of the over and du Plessis is on the move now. Another ball which is on the stumps line, du Plessis nicely flicks it. The ball races to the deep mid-wicket boundary.
Fuller one on off, du Plessis keeps it out.
Bouncer way over the head of ducking du Plessis. End of a top over for South Africa. Solid start of the session for them. 10 from the over.
Anderson starts with a poor ball down the leg side. Van der Dussen lets it go to the keeper.
Full one on middle, worked to mid-wicket.
Fuller and on off, van der Dussen does well to keep it out.
Good length ball coming into van der Dussen this time. He tucks it towards fine leg to get a run.
In the channel outside off, it is left alone.
Another leave as Anderson bowls this one on a good length outside off once again.
On the pads, Rassie tucks it towards mid-wicket and takes a quick single.
Fuller and around off, this time Faf pushes it wide of the cover fielder for a single.
Fuller and around off, it is defended.
Landed on a good length around off, van der Dussen looks to defend but the ball takes the inside half of the bat and goes to mid on.

On the pads again, van der Dussen looks to work it fine down the leg side but misses to get hit on the pads. The ball goes behind and before Buttler can pick the ball, the batters cross ends for a leg bye.
Back of a length ball around off, du Plessis drops his wrists and allows the ball to go the keeper.
Landed around off on a good length, van der Dussen defends it off the back foot.
Good length ball just outside off, Rassie has the stumps covered as he lets it go to the keeper.

Huge appeal but not out says the umpire. No review from England. A big inside edge there saves van der Dussen. Good call from England to not go for the review. It pitches around off and draws batsman half forward. Rassie pushes at the ball and luckily manages an inside edge onto the pads.
Full and outside off, pushed to point.
Shortish around off, van der Dussen stays on the back foot and blocks it towards point.
Fuller one just outside off, pushed to cover by Rassie.
On a good length on off, du Plessis keeps it out.
Good length delivery on middle, du Plessis defends it off the back foot.
Outside off, Faf leaves it alone.
On a good length on leg, du Plessis looks to flick but gets hit on the thigh pad.
BEATEN! An absolute jaffa from Archer. Slightly shortish length around off, du Plessis has to play at it. He hops a bit and pokes, luckily the ball goes a hint away and whizzes past the outside edge.
FOUR! Poor ball to finish the over. Short and wide outside off, du Plessis hammers it through the cover region. It races to the fence in a jiffy.
On a good length on off, van der Dussen defends it off the back foot.
Good length delivery on middle, Rassie defends it out.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Another ball which is outside off and it does not tempt van der Dussen into playing any fancy shot.
Beaten! Beauty from Anderson. It lands on a fuller length, van der Dussen this time goes for the drive but the ball shapes away and goes past the outside edge.
Good length ball around off,  it is blocked off the back foot.

NOT OUT! The decision is overturned and du Plessis survives. Very full and very wide from Archer. Du Plessis chases it and goes for the drive away from the body. He does not make any connection and Buttler behind the wicket catches and appeals along with Archer and the entire slip cordon. The umpire thinks and raises the finger. However, Faf does not think much and signals for the review straightaway. Let's see what the replays show. No problems with the front foot. Now, the Ultra Edge, there is a spike on it as the ball passes the bat but it is not sure from where it is coming from as there is a gap between the bat and ball. Tricky call for the third umpire to make. Not out is the decision from the third umpire then. Looks like a correct call has been made.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Landed on middle, worked to mid-wicket.
In the channel outside off, Faf makes a leave.
Fuller around off, pushed to cover.
Bouncer down the leg side. Du Plessis ducks under it.
Sam starts with a length delivery which nips back in to the right-hander. Van der Dussen defends it with a straight bat.

OUT! Caught! Yes, Sam can get the breakthrough. The bowling change does the trick for the visitors. The previous one came in to the right-hander, this one moves the other way. It is pitched on off, van der Dussen gets on his front foot and tries to play the classical front foot defense. The ball shapes away and finds the outside edge of the bat and goes straight towards first slip. England skipper, Joe Root there makes no mistake and takes a simple catch. Once again Curran gets the breakthrough. This young man has the knack of doing so and he is doing his reputation no harm. Not a long lasting start to his Test career for Rassie. Just 6 on his maiden outing.
Good length ball around off, de Kock taps it to point to start his innings.
Length delivery which comes back in on off. Quinton looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Back of a length on off, de Kock blocks it.

Good length ball outside off, de Kock taps it to the right of the fielder at point. Quinton comes out looking for a quick run but Faf straightaway turns it down. The fielder there makes a very good stop and has a shy at the keeper's end but misses. Even if he had hit, QdK would have been in.
Broad starts his new spell with a length ball away from the off pole. Du Plessis shoulders arms to it.
Once again Broad asks Faf to go for the drive by serving it outside off. Du Plessis has no interest to oblige to Broad's demand.
Broad goes full and on off. Faf pushes it to mid on.
Another one on the fourth stump line, Faf is happy to watch it carry to the keeper.
Outside off, Faf leaves it alone.
Good length ball on off, Faf defends it to get through the over.

FOUR! De Kock is off the mark in style. You give a southpaw some width outside off, he will punish you. If you give it to de Kock he will just oblige and hit you the way he wants. Good shot this. Length ball outside off, de Kock just hits it right off the middle through point for a boundary. 100 up for the Proteas.
FOUR! Now on the leg side. Curran is guilty of bowling on de Kock's pads. Quinton's eyes lit up looking at it and he flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Length ball on off, de Kock looks to defend but does so off the outer half of his bat.
Good length ball on off, de Kock blocks it.
FOUR! Third boundary of the over and de Kock is pouncing on all the mistakes from Curran. Once again Sam goes wide outside off, de Kock slashes it with ease and power through point for a boundary.
Length ball on off, de Kock punches it through extra cover and gets a couple to get through the over. Expensive from Sam Curran, 14 off it.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Absolute jaffa from Broad! Lands this one on a good length and on closer to off pole. The ball shapes away and goes past the outside edge of du Plessis.

OUT! Gone this time as the ball finds the edge this time. Broad follows the ripper with another one. He once again lands this one just around off. The ball once again shapes a hint away as du Plessis pokes at it by coming half forward. The ball this time takes the outside edge and goes to Root at first slip once again. The English skipper makes no mistake and takes the catch with ease. Faf departs after making a start and with it, half the side is back in the hut.
Pretorius is off the mark straightaway. A good length ball on middle, it is worked towards square leg for a single.
Fuller and outside off, driven to the fielder at short extra cover.

FOUR! De Kock seems to be playing on different surface. An overpitched ball alright but it still needs to be put away. He leans into the shot and slams this through covers. It whistles to the fence. Fourth boundary for de Kock in no time. However, end of a successful over by Broad.
On a good length on middle, Pretorius looks to flick but gets hit on the thigh pad.
Full delivery outside off, Pretorius drives it to point.
Good length delivery on middle, Pretorius defends it off the back foot.
Full delivery on middle, Pretorius drives it to mid on.
Full ball on off, pushed to mid on.
On middle, it is defended.
Broad starts the over by going full and outside off. He has seen de Kock going for the drive and that's why he tempts him there. Quinton though lets it go to the keeper
Outside off, this time de Kock shoulders arms.
Around off, defended towards mid off.
In the channel outside off. de Kock makes a leave.

Another nice drive from de Kock. A full ball outside off, de Kock drills it through covers. Denly from third man hares after the ball and makes a diving stop. The umpires are not sure if the attempt is clean as they refer it upstairs. The third umpire checks multiple replays and then deems it in the favour of the fielding side.
Another ball outside off, it is left alone.

Brilliant line and length from Curran. Another good length ball that pitches on middle and shapes away nicely. Pretorius looks to drive but makes no connection as the ball whizzes past the outside edge.
Around off and middle, pushed to point.
Loose from Pretorius. Curran goes fullish and outside off, inviting the batter for the drive. Pretorius does that and drives away from his body. He once again makes no connection.
Around off, it is defended.

Huge appeal for LBW but it dies down quickly. A fullish length ball on the pads, Pretorius looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. They appeal but the umpire says not out. Hawk Eye comes in and shows that it was pitching outside leg. So a good call once again from England skipper to not go for the review.
Shortish around off, Pretorius taps it towards the off side off the back foot.
FOUR! Poor start from Root as he dishes this way to outside off. De Kock reaches it out and guides it to third man fence.
Outside off, de Kock shoulders arms to this one.

In the air... but Anderson cannot reach there. The bait of coming to bowl almost paid off for Root. A flighted ball just outside off, inviting de Kock for the drive. He obliges and looks to slam it over long off. But the bat turns in his hand and he ends up lobbing the shot high towards mid off. Anderson hares from covers to get under the ball but he cannot get there and ends up missing out the chance of dismissing de Kock.
Flighted delivery on middle, Pretorius flicks it towards mid-wicket and takes a single.
Tossed up delivery on middle, de Kock defends it off the front foot.
Floated delivery on middle, de Kock flicks it through mid-wicket for a run.
Full delivery on off, de Kock drives it to covers.
On a good length on off, Quinton defends it off the back foot.
Good length delivery on middle, de Kock defends it out.
FOUR! Very well controlled pull from de Kock. Curran bangs it in short, Quinton picks it up early and gets on his back foot. He pulls it with control and power through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Good length delivery on middle, de Kock blocks it off the back foot.

INSIDE EDGE AND FOUR! Length ball outside off, De Kock throws his bat at it looking to slam it through point. The ball though takes the lower half of his bat and goes to the right of the keeper. Buttler is wrong-footed and he dives but he cannot save it. The ball races away to the fine leg fence.
Floated delivery on middle, Pretorius drives it through mid on for a single.
Tossed up delivery outside off, de Kock drives it through covers. The batsmen take a single.
SIX! Oh that is a monster. Floated on middle and off, Pretorius who is known for his T20 exploits shows what he is capable of as he hammers it over the long on fence, using the arc for a biggie.
Follows the maximum with an easy single towards cover.

Just shot! It has not carried. Slightly quicker from Root around off. De Kock looks to defend but the ball spins away from him. It takes the outside edge and goes towards first slip. Ben Stokes there looks to take it on the full, inches above the ground but looks like it has fallen short judging by Root and Stokes' reaction. The umpire takes it upstairs with the soft signal as 'Not Out'. Replay rolls in and it shows that the ball fell just short as it goes into the hands of Stokes.
Floated on off, de Kock plays it towards cover and keeps the strike with a single.
Outside off, de Kock offers no shot to this one.

FOUR! Up and over! De Kock is no mood to calm down as he once again throws his willow to this fuller ball outside off. This time the ball takes the outside edge and it flies over the slip cordon and into the fence.
Slightly short and just outside off this time, de Kock shoulders arms to this one.

EDGY FOUR! Another one off the outside edge! 150 comes up for South Africa. Another fuller ball which is just outside off. De Kock once again goes for the drive. The ball takes the outside edge and goes to the third man fence, past the diving attempt of the gully fielder. 9th boundary for de Kock.
Fuller and around off, pushed through point for a single.
Good length ball around off, pushed to point.
Tossed up delivery on off, de Kock defends it off the front foot.
Flighted delivery on middle, de Kock sweeps it towards the leg side.
Floated delivery on middle, de Kock sweeps it to mid-wicket.
What was that! Another ball outside off, a tossed up one too. De Kock goes for the sweep again but the ball takes the outside edge and goes over the leaping Ben Stokes. A couple of runs.
Loopy delivery on middle, de Kock drives it through covers. The batsmen get two runs.
Flighted delivery on off, Quinton offers a forward defense on this one.
In the channel outside off, Pretorius makes a leave by covering his stumps.

Edgy FOUR! Now the edge flies to the fence off Pretorius' bat. A full ball outside off, Pretorius goes for the drive away from the body. The ball takes the outside edge and goes to the third man fence.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Full and on off, pushed towards cover for a single. 50-run stand is up between the two and these runs have come in quick time and against the run of play.
Fuller around off, pushed to cover by de Kock.

There it is. Fifty for Quinton de Kock, his 18th in Tests. A brilliant hand this from Quinton. A short ball on middle, de Kock pulls it towards mid-wicket and takes a run to reach the landmark. Brilliant attacking innings and he would be looking to reach the three figure mark from hereon.
Tossed up delivery on off, de Kock plays it to point.
Flighted delivery on off, Quinton taps it to point.
Loopy delivery on middle, de Kock blocks it off the back foot.
Floated delivery on off, Quinton punches it to point.
Floated delivery on off, Quinton drives it through covers. The batsmen take a run.

FOUR! Just short! Floated on off, Pretorius lofts it over long off. It looks like the ball hits the ropes on the full but the umpires go upstairs to check if that has hit the rope or not. Replay rolls in and after a few views the third umpire says it is a boundary to the on-field umpire as the ball hit the turf just before the ropes.
In the channel outside off, it is left alone.
Another ball outside off, de Kock makes second leave of the over.
Fuller around off, pushed to covers.
Good length ball on the pads, de Kock works it behind square leg for a single.
Landed outside off on a good length, Pretorius lets it go to the keeper.
Shortish ball around off, Pretorius taps it through point and takes a couple of runs.
Broad starts with a good length ball around off, de Kock pushes it back to the bowler.

Brilliant fielding from Bairstow! A full ball around off, de Kock whips it through mid-wicket. Bairstow from mid on chases the ball down and then makes a diving stop just before the ropes. Saves a single and then quickly gets up and throws the ball to the keeper.
On the pads, Pretorius flicks but misses to get hit on the pads. A stifled appeal but it clearly looked to be going down the leg side and hit high too.
Outside off, Pretorius lets it go to the keeper.
Fuller and on off, driven to long off.
On middle, it is defended.
BEATEN! Loose shot from Quinton. Full and outside off, de Kock looks to play away from the body but misses it.
FOUR! Poor line from Archer. He bowls it full but too straight. De Kock simply flicks it to the fine leg fence.
On a good length on off, de Kock offers a solid defense on this one.
Length delivery on middle, Quinton flicks it to mid-wicket.
BEATEN! Beauty of a delivery! On a good length and outside off, de Kock looks to defend but misses it.
Almost dragged on! Good length delivery on off, Quinton looks to cut but gets an inside edge on this one. It just misses the leg stump.
Outside off, de Kock offers no shot to this one.
Full delivery on off, Pretorius drives it to covers.
Outside off, Dwaine shoulders arms to this one.
FOUR! Uppish but flicked nicely! A fuller ball on middle, Pretorius flicks it between short mid-wicket and mid on. Timed it brilliantly.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Fuller and on off, driven towards mid on by Pretorius.

FOUR! Glorious from de Kock! Just a push but it races to the fence. Fullish length ball on off, de Kock comes forward a hint and presents the full face of the bat. It races to the mid on fence quickly. Looking in a brilliant nick there, is de Kock.
Bowls a bouncer outside off, de Kock sways away from it.
NO BALL! Archer oversteps! On a good length on off, de Kock defends it off the back foot.
Good length delivery on off, Quinton blocks it well.
Outside off, Quinton shoulders arms to this one.
Again outside off, de Kock leaves it alone.
On a length on middle, de Kock flicks it through square leg for a single. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 1!
Run straightaway in the final session. Good length ball outside off, de Kock punches it to deep point and gets a single.
Closer to the off pole from Sam. Dwaine defends it confidently towards cover-point and calls a loud wait.
On the leg side but close to the body. Pretorius looks to tickle it fine down the leg side but misses. There is a stifled appeal from the English players but the umpire says no.

Pretorius gets off the mark for the session. Full on off, Dwaine pushes it to the right of mid off and calls for a quick single. Archer gets to the ball and has a shy at the bowler's end but misses. Even if he had hit, DP would have been in.
Back of a length around off, de Kock looks to flick but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Good length ball on off, de Kock defends it towards mid on.
Good length ball on middle, Pretorius tucks it behind square leg for a single.
Full and on middle, de Kock flicks but can't beat the mid-wicket fielder.
Good length ball outside off, de Kock cuts but finds the gully fielder this time.
Full and on the pads again, this time de Kock's flick goes to deep square leg and the batters cross ends.
Shortish and on middle, Pretorius goes on the back foot and pushes it towards cover.
BEATEN! On a good length and outside off, Pretorius looks to defend but misses it.
Short and wide outside off, de Kock cuts it through point for a single.
FOUR! Hammered! A short ball outside off, Pretorius goes on the back foot and slams it wide of the mid on fence.
Now a couple to fine leg. A delivery on the pads of Pretorius clips it towards fine leg. The deep square leg fielder dives and makes a fine stop.

NOT OUT! Pitching outside leg and Pretorius stays. England though loses the review. A fullish length ball on the pads, Pretorius looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. Curran along with the wicket keeper and entire slip cordon appeal but the umpire is unmoved. After a long chat, Root signals the 'T' and takes the decision upstairs. Here comes the replays, the front foot is okay. Hawk Eye time now, well, it has pitched outside leg so no need to check where it is hitting. England lose their one of the two reviews.

OUT! Caught! Once again it is Sam Curran who has got the breakthrough.  Brilliant ball this from Curran. Good length ball around off, in the channel of uncertainty. Pretorius expects the ball to come in but it goes away with the angle. Dwaine looks to defend hoping that it would shape in but it does not. He ends up getting a thick outside edge which goes straight to the man at first slip. Joe Root there takes another simple catch, his third of the innings. They lost one of their reviews in the previous ball but it has not cost them a lot as he has struck gold in the very next ball. The 87-run stand is broken and England have their first wicket of the session.
Full on the pads, Philander flicks but Sibley at short mid-wicket makes an excellent stop diving to his right.
On a good length on middle, de Kock drives it back towards the bowler.

Edged but safe. What a delivery this is from Jofra. Trademark Archer this. Hits the deck hard on off and the ball shoots up off the surface. It is bowled at 140 kph but it looks like it comes a lot quicker than that. De Kock looks to defend on the on side but it rises on him and the ball hits the top of the bat. Luckily for Quinton and South Africa it falls in no man's land at point.
Short delivery on middle, de Kock pulls it through square leg for a single.
Outside off, Philander offers no shot to this one.
On a good length on off, Philander keeps it out.
Good length delivery on leg, Vernon keeps it out.
Full delivery on off, de Kock plays it to mid off.
Length delivery on middle, de Kock nudges it towards square leg. The batsmen take a single.
Full delivery on middle, Philander drives it to mid on.
FOUR! Nice way to get off the mark. Slightly fuller ball outside off, Philander comes forward and slams it through covers for a boundary.
Around off, it is defended.

Huge appeal for LBW but  nothing from the umpire. Curran goes full and on the stumps line, Philander looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. Curran makes a loud appeal but the umpire is unmoved. This time Root does not go for the review.
BEATEN! Short and outside off, de Kock looks to cut but misses it.
On a good length on leg, de Kock looks to flick but gets it off the thigh pad. It goes towards the leg side. The batsmen take a run. The umpire gives it as a leg bye.
Length delivery on off, Philander taps it towards point. The batsmen take a run.
On a good length on middle, Quinton blocks it off the back foot.
BEATEN! Short and outside off, de Kock looks to play an upper cut but misses it.
On a length on middle, de Kock nudges it towards square leg for a run.
Full delivery on off, de Kock drives it back towards the bowler.
Good length delivery on middle, Quinton blocks it off the back foot.
WIDE! Bowls it wide outside off, de Kock does not bother to play at that.
On a good length on off, de Kock defends it off the back foot.
Good length delivery on middle, Quinton defends it off the back foot.
On a good length on off, de Kock looks to defend but gets a bottom edge on this one.
Full delivery on off, de Kock drives it to mid off.
Bowls a bouncer outside off, Philander lets it sail through to the keeper.
Length delivery on off, Philander taps it to point.
On a good length and outside off, Philander looks to cut but gets a bottom edge on this one.
Bowls a bumper outside off, Philander watches it sail through to the keeper.
Outside off, Vernon offers no shot to this one.
Good length delivery on off, Philander blocks it off the back foot.
On a length on middle, de Kock flicks it through mid-wicket. The batsmen get two runs.
Length delivery on middle, Quinton flicks it through mid-wicket. The batsmen take a run.
Outside off, de Kock shoulders arms to this one.
Bowls a yorker on middle, Philander does well to dig it out.
Full delivery on off, Philander drives it to mid off.
On a length on middle, Philander tucks it towards the leg side.
Full delivery outside off, de Kock offers no shot to this one.
On a good length on off, de Kock blocks it off the back foot.
Full delivery on middle, de Kock looks to drive but gets it off the inner half of the bat. It goes to mid on.
Good length delivery on off, de Kock defends it off the front foot.
Outside off, Quinton leaves it alone.
On a good length on middle, de Kock looks to defend but gets an inside edge. It misses the leg stump and it goes towards fine leg. The batsmen take a run.

EDGY FOUR! Shout for catch but nobody will as it lands uppishly in no man's land and ends up going to the third man fence. A fuller ball outside off to start the fresh over. De Kock reaches out and goes for the drive away from his body. The ball takes thick outside edge and goes to third man fence.
Around off, pushed to mid on.

Appeal for LBW but nothing from the umpire. Good length ball around the pads, de Kock looks to work it on the leg side but misses to get hit on the pads. An appeal follows but nothing from the umpire. No DRS from England either and replays roll in and suggest it to be a good call as the ball pitched outside leg.
Full and on middle, flicked straight to mid on.
Another fullish ball around off and middle, de Kock tucks it towards mid on.
On the pads again, de Kock looks to work it to the leg side but the ball hits is pads and goes towards square leg. The batters cross for a leg bye.
Short and outside off, de Kock cuts it through point. The batsmen take a single.
On a good length on off, Philander looks to defend but gets hit on the hand. That could be nasty.
Good length delivery on middle, Philander blocks it off the back foot.
Length delivery on off, Philander taps it to point.
On a good length on off, Vernon blocks it well.
FOUR! On a good length and outside off, Philander looks to punch but gets an outside edge. It goes towards third man for a boundary.
Outside off, Quinton does not bother to play at that.

FOUR! Another edgy boundary! Short and outside off, de Kock looks to slash but gets an outside edge. It goes over the slip region and towards third man for a boundary. He moves into the 80s with that boundary.
Fuller and on off, de Kock works it towards wide mid on and scampers for a couple of runs.
Full delivery outside off, de Kock drives it to mid off.
Full again on off, Quinton plays it to covers.
On a good length on off, Quinton blocks it off the back foot.
Length delivery on middle, Philander flicks it through square leg for a run.
FOUR! Classic shot. Full and outside off, de Kock drives it through mid off for a boundary.
On a good length on off, de Kock taps it towards the off side.
On a length on leg, de Kock flicks it towards fine leg for a run.
Bowls it wide outside off, Philander shoulders arms to this one.
Good length delivery on off, Philander defends it out.
Full delivery on middle, de Kock flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.
Outside off, Philander offers no shot on this one.
Again outside off, Philander shoulders arms to this one.
Good length delivery on middle, Vernon blocks it off the back foot.
Outside off, Philander leaves it alone.
On a good length on middle, Philander looks to defend but gets hit on the thigh pad. The bowler appeals for lbw but the umpire shakes his head.
Good length ball around off, de Kock pushes it to cover.
Length delivery outside off, de Kock strokes it through point for a single.
Back of a length on off, Philander hops up and keeps the ball down with a straight bat.
Good leave. Length ball swinging in from outside off. Philander reads it well and offers a very solid leave as the ball goes past the stump.
Length ball around off, Philander defends it solidly from within the crease.
A little bit of an extra bounce to end the over. Good length ball outside off, Philander looks to play it with a slant bat but misses.
Denly starts with a flighted ball on the pads, de Kock turns it behind square on the leg side and gets a single to move to 93.
Flatter on off, Philander hits it straight back to the bowler.
Tossed up on off, Philander hits it straight to the left of the bowler. Denly gets down and deflects it towards mid on. Does not cost any runs.
Flighted and turning away sharply from VP. He does well to defend it.
Flighted leg spinner on the stumps, Vernon keeps it out.
Around the pads, Philander flicks it to mid-wicket to get through the over.
Full and outside off, de Kock defends it off the front foot towards cover.
Full and coming in with the angle. It is on middle, de Kock flicks it to square leg and gets a single.
BEATEN! On a good length and outside off, Philander looks to defend but misses it.
FOUR! Nice shot. On a good length on off, Philander guides it towards third man for a boundary.
Outside off, Vernon lets it go.
Again outside off, Philander shoulders arms to this one.
Flighted delivery on leg, de Kock drives it through mid on. The batsmen take a single.
Tossed up delivery on off, Philander drives it through mid off for a run.
Floated delivery on middle, Quinton blocks it off the back foot.
Loopy delivery on middle, de Kock keeps it out.
Flighted delivery on middle, de Kock defends it out.
Full delivery on off, de Kock drives it to covers.
Full delivery on off, Philander drives it to mid off.
On a good length on off, Vernon keeps it out.
Good length delivery on middle, Philander blocks it well.
Bouncer! A well directed one from Curran. It is right around the body line but Vernon sits under it but the ball clips his bat and goes towards fine leg and they take a run.

OUT! Caught behind! De Kock falls in nervous 90s and he misses out on a well deserved hundred here. Big wicket and once again it is Sam Curran who has given Root the breakthrough. This young lad is some cricketer. His 4th wicket of the innings. Good length ball around off and shaping away. De Kock looks to defend it away from the body but the ball kisses the outside edge of the willow and goes straight into the mitts of Buttler. The 47-run stand is broken and England have a chance now to wrap this up and maybe even bat again for an over or two. There was no need for de Kock to have a feel of that but he still went for it and he will be gutted with himself to miss out on a deserving ton. He walks off to an applause from the crowd and his teammates alike. He has single-handedly taken the hosts to a very good, fighting total here. Quinton will not be happy having missed out on his personal milestone.
Maharaj is off the mark. Good length ball which shapes in viciously. Keshav does well to flick it late on to the on side and get a single.
Outside off, Maharaj shoulders arms to this one.
Full delivery on off, Maharaj drives it to mid off.
Bowls a bouncer, Maharaj does well to duck under it.
Outside off, Keshav leaves it alone.
Bowls a bouncer outside off, Maharaj lets it sail through to the keeper.
Outside off, Maharaj offers no shot to this one.
On a good length on off, Philander defends it off the back foot.
Full delivery on off, Philander drives it through point for a single.

NOT OUT! There is a clear inside edge on this one as Ultra Edge detects. On a good length on middle, Maharaj looks to flick but gets hit on the pads. The bowler appeals for lbw and the umpire raises his finger. Maharaj straightaway takes the review. Ultra Edge clearly detects an inside edge.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
On the pads, Maharaj flicks it to fine leg for a single.
Outside off, it is left alone.
FOUR! That is put away! Short and outside off, Maharaj cuts it hard through point for a boundary.
Bowls a bouncer, Maharaj does well to duck under it.
Outside off, Keshav leaves it alone.
On a good length and outside off, Maharaj does not bother to play at that.

OUT! Yes, the soft signal stays and Jofra has a wicket, he finally has one. A shortish length ball just around off, Maharaj plays looks to defend it coming forward. The ball takes the outside edge and goes low to Ben Stokes who pouches it inches above the turf. Maharaj is not sure if that carried to Stokes and he stands waiting. The umpire refers it upstairs with the soft signal being out. First the front foot is getting checked, it is fine. Now, did that carry? Yes, it did, Stokes did really well to get his fingers under the ball and grab it safely. England are just two away from bundling the hosts.
On a good length on off, Rabada defends it off the front foot.
Length delivery on off, Philander taps it through point for a single.
On a good length on off, Rabada defends it off the back foot.
Good length delivery on off, Rabada keeps it out.
Bowls a bouncer, Rabada ducks under it.
Length delivery on middle, Kagiso nudges it towards the leg side.
On a good length on off, Rabada looks to defend but gets hit on the hand.
Outside off, Philander offers no shot to this one.
On a good length on off, Philander taps it to point.
Length delivery on off, Philander plays it to covers.
FOUR! That is punished! Short and outside off, Philander cuts it hard through point for a boundary.
Bowls a bouncer, Philander ducks under it.
Short delivery on leg, Philander looks to flick but gets hit on the thigh pad.
On a good length on off, Rabada defends it off the back foot.
Bowls a yorker on middle, Rabada does well to dig it out.
FOUR! On a good length and outside off, Rabada looks to defend but gets an outside edge. It goes towards third man for a boundary.
Full delivery on middle, Rabada drives it back towards the bowler.
Good length delivery on middle, Kagiso blocks it well.
On a good length on off, Rabada defends it out.
Good length delivery on off, Philander offers a back foot defense on this one.
On a length on off, Philander plays it to point.
Full delivery on off, Vernon drives it to covers.
Bowls a bouncer, Philander does well to duck under it.
Length delivery on middle, Philander flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.
BEATEN! On a good length and outside off, Rabada looks to defend but misses it.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Philander drives it to mid on.
Flighted delivery on middle, Vernon drives it towards mid on.
Loopy delivery outside off, Philander shoulders arms to this one.
Floated delivery on middle, Philander flicks it through mid-wicket for a run.
Tossed up delivery on off, Rabada keeps it out.
Flighted delivery on middle, Rabada defends it off the back foot.
On a good length on off, Philander defends it off the back foot.
Full delivery on middle, Philander flicks it to mid-wicket.
On a good length on off, Philander keeps it out.
Bowls it down the leg side, Philander looks to flick but misses it.
BEATEN! On a good length and outside off, Philander looks to defend but misses it.
FOUR! Terrific shot. Full delivery outside off, Philander drives it through covers for a boundary.
In the channel outside off, Rabada lets it be.
Another good length ball outside off, Rabada covers his stumps and lets it go to the keeper.
FOUR! Nicely done! A fuller ball outside off, Rabada gets his bat down and guides it between gully and point. It races to the third man fence and Rabada has his second boundary.
Around off, it is defended off the back foot towards cover.
Landed around off on a shortish length, Rabada keeps it out.

FOUR! Brilliant drive and it reaches the fence. A fuller ball outside off again, Rabada drills it towards cover. The fielder there makes a half stop diving to his right but this has been drilled really hard. The ball eventually reaches the fence before the fielder can chase it down. Second boundary of the over for Rabada. These are very valuable runs for South Africa.
On a good length on leg, Philander looks to flick but gets it off the pads. It goes towards the leg side. The batsmen take a single. The umpire gives it as a leg bye.
WIDE! Bowls it wide outside off, Rabada does not bother to play at that.
Outside off, Rabada leaves it alone.
On a good length on off, Rabada blocks it off the back foot.

OUT! Through the gates! Superb from Broad. And South Africa lose the 9th wicket. A brilliant ball that pitches around off and comes back in with the angle. Rabada looks to defend  but the ball comes back in sharply to beat the inside edge of the bat. It brushes the thigh pad and then goes to disturb the timbers behind. And, with that the umpires have called for STUMPS ON DAY 1.
Broad starts the day with a back of a length ball but it is way too wide outside off to trouble Nortje. He drops his wrists and lets it go to the keeper.
Another ball which is outside off on a good length. It is easily left alone by Nortje.
Fuller ball from Curran to start his spell on a fresh day. Philander pushes it to mid off.
Good length ball around off, Vernon pushes it towards cover and takes a single.
Good length ball angled away from the right-hander. Nortje makes a leave.
Beaten! A full ball just outside off this time. Nortje this time is lured into the shot. He drives but makes no connection.
In the channel outside off, Nortje covers his stumps and shoulders arms.
Fuller and on off, Nortje comes forward and defends it towards mid off.
FOUR! Nicely done and important runs these. A short ball outside off, Philander goes back and slashes it wide of the gully fielder. It races to the third man fence.

A better throw would've made things interesting but two runs for Philander and South Africa nonetheless. A good length ball just around off, Philander pushes it through covers and looks to take two. Nortje is little slow in responding and the throw from sweeper cover comes but Broad is in front of the stumps to collect. He ends up disturbing the stumps with his hands.

OUT! Caught! There is a spike on Ultra Edge and Philander has to go. A good length ball which is outside off and it is shaping further away from Philander. He pokes at it away from his body and ends up nicking behind. Buttler catches it and celebrates. The umpire raises his finger but Philander goes for the review. Probably because it is there at his disposal. Don't think it is going to save him though. Here comes the replay. The front foot is okay. There seem to be a deflection as the ball passes the bat and the Ultra Edge clearly detects it. The decision stays OUT and that is the end of the innings for South Africa. 284/10 IT IS.

NOT OUT! Excellent review and actually the credit has to be given to Sibley. Burns was not sure whether the ball had kissed the bat or not so he reviewed it after having a brief chat with Dominic. South Africa almost had a perfect start just like England. Full and swinging away from the southpaw. Burns looks to drive it straight but misses. There is a noise as the ball goes to the keeper. De Kock takes the catch and goes up in a confident appeal. The umpire agrees and raises his finger. Burns is unsure and has a word with his partner. After consulting Sibley, Rory signals the 'T'. Replay rolls in and it shows that the ball has missed the bat and the sound is of the bat hitting the pad. Ultra Edge rolls in and it shows that there is a very little spike as the ball goes past the bat but there is also a gap so the on-field decision has to be reversed.
Wild ball. Length ball way outside off, Burns has no interest in playing that.
NO BALL! Poor start for Rabada. After the first ball he has gone way wide outside off, Burns shoulders arms to it. Rabada has overstepped and it has been caught by the umpire.

NO BALL AND FOUR! Superb ball this but Rabada has overstepped here. Full and swinging in on off. Burns looks to play it on the on side but the ball goes off the outside edge through the gully region for a boundary. First runs off the bat.
On the pads, Burns looks to flick but misses and the ball hits the thigh pad.
Good length ball outside off, Burns looks to defend but misses.
On the pads, Burns once again looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads.
Just short! Rabada fires one on the pads, Burns looks to flick but it goes off the edge and falls short of the diving man at short leg.
Philander starts with a good length ball around off, it shapes away from Sibley. He lets it go to the keeper.
Fullish one around off, it is defended.
Another length ball which is closer to off pole than the previous one but not enough to make Sibley play at it.
In the channel outside off, Sibley makes another leave.

Just short! Brilliant line this from Philander. A good length ball around off, Sibley this time pokes at the ball but with soft hands. The ball takes the outside edge and goes to du Plessis at the second slip but on the bounce. Soft hands saved Sibley there.
Sibley makes another leave as Philander lands this one outside off on a good length.
Back of a length ball outside off, Burns sways away from it.

Bounce, pace and good carry on this one. Excellent ball. Rabada steams in and hits the deck hard with a 143 kph delivery around off. Burns looks to defend but the ball shapes away squaring Rory all ends up. It shoots on its way to the keeper and reaches Quinton over his head.
Bouncer! A very well directed one. It is right around his eye line. Burns does well to sway away from it.

EDGED AND FOUR! Rabada is troubling Burns in every possible way here. Full and swinging away. Burns looks to drive it to the on side but gets squared up. It goes off the outside edge through the backward point region for a boundary.
A good solid front foot defense from Burns. On the stumps, RB blocks it.
On the pads, Burns tucks it to the leg side and keeps the strike.

OUT! Caught behind! This time there is no need to review it as Burns knows he has got something on it. Absolute jaffa from Vernon Philander. He is one of the best bowler to left-handers and he has struck gold in the very second over here with a peach. Vernon bowls it on a length, in the channel of uncertainty. The ball goes with the angle but then straightens a bit. Rory looks to defend but gets a feather on it of his glove on its way to the keeper. De Kock takes it and goes up in celebration. Burns does not even wait for long and starts walking back. South Africa needed early wicket and they have got just that. Perfect start for Philander in his final series.
Good length ball outside off, Denly shoulders arms to it.
Good ball this. Inswinging from off, JD looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto his pads.
On the pads, Denly glances it to mid-wicket.
Back of a length on off, Denly defends it off his back foot.
Length delivery on off, Denly gets right behind the line of the ball and defends it with a straight bat. End of a very successful over from VP.
On a good length on leg, Sibley flicks it towards the leg side.
Outside off, Sibley shoulders arms to this one.
Bowls it down the leg side, Sibley lets it go.
BEATEN! Good shape on this one! On a good length and outside off, Sibley looks to defend but misses it.
FOUR! Flicked nicely! First boundary for Sibley! A fullish ball on middle of the right-hander. Sibley is really strong on anything on the pads. He flicks it to the mid-wicket fence nicely.

OUT! Caught! Some drama though! Sibley has been given not out by the umpire. Faf du Plessis without even having a word with the bowler signals the 'T' straightaway. However, after he takes the DRS, Sibley starts going off. He did not do that immediately but after the decision has been taken upstairs, he starts walking. The umpire there stops him, probably to get everything confirmed. Now, time for the replays, front foot is okay. And a clear spike on the Ultra Edge. So, now, please keep walking, Mr. Sibley. Coming to the ball, whatta ripper from Rabada. Back of a length ball around off, the right-hander has to play at it. Sibley hops and pokes at the ball but only manages an outside edge to the keeper. England are in all sorts of trouble early on.
On the pads, Denly looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads.
Once again it is on the pads, Denly looks to flick but once again misses.

Close, close call this. Looks like height has saved Denly. Good length ball pitching on off and middle and jagging back in. Denly looks to defend but misses. The ball hits him over the knee roll and there is a huge appeal. The umpire though does not agree and shakes it away. Faf du Plessis does not review it and it is a good decision as the Hawk Eye later on shows that the ball was going to miss the stumps.
On the fourth stump line, Denly leaves it alone.
Away from the off pole, JD shoulders arms to it.
Beauty to finish the over! Good length ball around off, the ball zips away a bit. Denly looks to defend but gets beaten.
In the channel outside off, Root covers his sticks and lets it be.

Another peach from Rabada! Fullish ball, closer to off pole. Root without moving his feet pushes at the ball with hard hands. He makes no connection and is beaten for the outside edge. Could've easily gone on to hit the off pole there.
A brilliant bouncer now! It is on the body of Root. He hops and looks to fend it away. The ball hits the handle of the bat and goes to fine leg for a couple of runs.
Another play and a miss! A good length ball in the channel outside off, Root once again feels for the ball and goes for the drive. Only to get beaten. Lucky not to edge that one.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Shortish ball on off, Root goes on the back foot and defends it out. Testing over this from Rabada.
Fuller around off, Denly comes forward and pushes it towards cover.
Landed around off, it is blocked by Denly. Still searching for that run to get off the mark.

Soft hands again! A good length ball around off, Denly waits for the ball to come to him and defends. The ball takes outside edge and goes towards second slip. The fielder there dives to his right to stop the ball.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Outside off, Denly makes a leave.
Fullish ball inviting for the drive but Denly is not lured into the shot. He lets it go to the keeper.
FOUR! Timed superbly! Rabada bowls it full around off, Root comes forward and punches it through point for his first boundary.
Bumper which goes way to high and it is outside off too. Root shows no interest.
Angled into the batsman this time from a good length. Root looks to tuck it towards the leg side but ends up getting hit high on the thigh pads.

FOUR LEG BYES! But off the helmet. A well directed bouncer from Rabada. Root is late in ducking under it. The ball hits the helmet and goes to to third man fence over the slip cordon. Root takes his helmet off and checks it. He seems fine.
Good length ball outside off, Root does not disturb that.
Another length delivery outside off, it swings back in after the stumps. Root leaves it alone.
Around off, it is defended off the front foot.
In the channel outside off, it is left alone.
Full and around off, Denly looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Good length ball around off, Denly looks to leave the ball first but is late in removing his bat down. Ends up tapping it towards the off side.
Fuller ball on middle, Denly looks to flick but misses. The ball hits the pads and goes fine leg for of leg byes. Still trying to get off the mark.
Landed around off, Root comes forward and defends. 5 maidens in a row from Philander. He has be so accurate in this spell.
Shortish around middle, pushed to mid on.
Good length ball around off and middle, it is defended.

Dropped! Initially, it looked like it did not carry but it did. Oh, dear! Van der Dussen is the man. Probably de Kock came in the way as he dived to his right to pouch the ball. A brilliant ball from Rabada once again and he cannot believe it as he has his face covered with his hands. A back of a length ball outside off, Denly pokes at it. The ball takes the outside edge and goes towards the first slip. De Kock throws himself to his right but cannot reach there. The ball goes in the hands of debutant Rassie but it quickly pops out. It went straight in so one would feel he should've had taken it. Probably the dive of de Kock distracted him there. It can be really costly because Denly can get himself in and play a really big knock.
Sprayed down the leg side. Denly looks to flick but misses.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Denly is off the mark and the crowd applause. A good length ball around off, Denly taps it towards cover. 28th ball it is and Denly has a run.
In the channel outside off to bowl the first ever ball in Tests from Pretorius. It is left alone.
On middle, tucked towards mid-wicket.
Another ball outside off, it is left alone.
On a good length on off, Denly defends it off the back foot.
Good length delivery on off, Joe blocks it off the back foot.
Just away from the stumps. Good length ball on off, Denly looks to defend but he is a bit late on it. It hits the upper part of his bat and rolls behind. It goes past the stumps by just mere inches.
Nortje starts with a back of a length ball outside off. He bowls this at 147 kph and makes the ball shoot up off the deck. Root leaves it alone.
On a good length on off, Root defends it to covers.
Good length delivery on off, Root taps it to point.

A very intent-ful bouncer but good take from Quinton de Kock. It is around off, Root ducks under it. The ball keeps getting high on de Kock. He jumps, one might feel he even flew there to take it and save runs for his side.
Outside off, Root shoulders arms to this one.

FOUR! Educational edge this from Root! A 149 kph delivery bowled on a length around off, Root looks to defend but opens the face of the bat in the last moment to send it wide of the man at gully and the ball races away to the fence.
Outside off, Denly does not bother to play at that.
On a good length on off, Denly defends it off the front foot.
Length delivery on off, Denly looks to defend but gets an outside edge. It goes towards third man. The batsmen get two runs.
Full delivery on middle, Denly flicks it to mid-wicket.
On a good length on off, Denly blocks it well.
Good length delivery on middle, Denly keeps it out.
FOUR! Length delivery outside off, Root goes on the back foot and punches it past the diving gully fielder towards third man for a boundary.
On a good length on off, Root blocks it off the back foot.
Good length delivery on middle, Root defends it off the back foot.
Short delivery on off, Root cuts it to point.
Good length delivery outside off, Root taps it towards covers and takes a run.
A real spicy delivery this from Nortje. Touches 150kph. It is on the pads, Denly looks to flick but misses. Nortje goes up in appeal but the umpire says no.
On a good length on off, the skipper defends it off the back foot.
Full delivery on middle, Root plays it to mid on.
On a good length on off, Root defends it off the front foot.
On middle, Root offers a back foot defense on this one.
Length delivery on off, Root punches it to point.
FOUR! Nicely played! On a good length on off, Root plays it with soft hands and guides it towards third man for a boundary.
FOUR! First one for him. That was boundary the moment it left the bat. A good length on middle, Denly uses his wrists and whips it to deep mid-wicket fence. That raced to the fence in a jiffy.
Good length delivery on middle, Denly blocks it off the back foot.
BEATEN! On a good length and outside off, Denly looks to defend but misses it.
FOUR! Nice shot. Second boundary of the over. Full delivery on middle, Denly drives it through mid on for a boundary. 50 up for England.
Length delivery on off, Denly plays it towards covers. The batsmen take a run.

Huge appeal for LBW but the umpire shakes it away. Very good ball this from Nortje. Pacy and coming in, Root looks to defend but it hits him on the pads. There is a huge appeal from the Proteas players but the umpire is not interested. Faf du Plessis does not go for the review as they feel there is a slight inside edge on this.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Fuller around off, pushed to covers.
Full and on the stumps, Denly drives it to mid on where Rabada fumbles but no runs taken.

FOUR! Clipped nicely! A good length ball on middle, Denly is very strong there. He flicks it with power and it beats the mid-wicket fielder and races to the fence. He is starting to look settled out in the middle now.
Good leave now! A ball on a good length and in the channel. Denly covers his stumps and lets it go to the keeper.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Full delivery outside off, Root drives it through point. Maharaj chases it and does well to stop it. The batsmen pick up a couple.
On a good length on off, Root blocks it off the back foot.
Bowls a bouncer, Root does well to duck under it.
On a length on middle, the skipper flicks it to mid-wicket.
Bowls a quick bouncer on leg, Root ducks under it. It goes to de Kock who makes a one-handed stop.
Good length delivery on off, Root defends it out.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Denly defends it off the front foot.
Flighted delivery on off, Denly blocks it off the back foot.
Loopy delivery on middle, Denly blocks it off the front foot.
Floated delivery on off, Denly keeps it out.
Tossed up delivery on middle and leg, Denly offers a forward defense on this one.
Flighted delivery on off, Denly keeps it out.
On a good length on off, Root plays it towards point. The batsmen take a single.
Good length delivery on off, Denly blocks it off the front foot.
Bowls a bumper, Denly ducks under it.
On a length on middle, Denly drives it towards mid on for a run.
Outside off, the skipper leaves it alone.
Length delivery on off, Root pushes it towards covers. The batsmen cross ends. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 2!
Good length ball around off, pushed to covers by Root.
Root was in two minds there. A shortish length ball just outside off, Root first thinks to defend but at the last moment pulls his bat out of the line of the ball.

Beaten! This time he plays the defensive shot but is beaten. Kept slightly low as well. Another good length ball which is in the channel outside off. Root does not move his feet at all and drives to get beaten.
First runs off Philander after 33 dot balls. Brilliant stuff so far from Vernon. A good length ball around middle, Root takes a step forward and tucks it towards the leg side for a single.
Good length ball around off, it is blocked.
Good length ball outside off, Denly stays on the back foot and pushes it towards cover.
FOUR! Shot! A short ball outside off to start the fresh over. Root goes on the back foot and slashes it past point. It races to the fence.
On middle, Root defends it off the back foot.
Shortish outside off again, Root hops and pushes it towards point.
Shortish around off again, Root goes on the back foot and taps it towards cover and takes off for a single. Maharaj gets to the ball and has a shy at the striker's end but misses.
Around off, it is defended.
FOUR! Glorious! Overpitched from Rabada and Denly pounces on it. He leans into the shot and creams it through covers.

OUT! The England skipper is out of here and it is a body blow for England. Brilliant from Philander once again. Spot on with his line and length once again. Another ball in the channel outside off, Root can easily leave these alone. He though decides to have a poke at it. Joe ends up getting a tickle behind the wicket. De Kock takes the catch and celebrates. The umpire too raises the finger instantly and Root walks off. As he goes to the pavilion, punches his bat. Did all the hard work and then threw it away.
Landed on middle, it is defended.
On middle again, Stokes is right behind the line of the delivery to defend.
Outside off for the left-hander and on a good length, Stokes allows it to go to the keeper.
Another ball outside off which is shaping away from the left-hander. Stokes has his stumps covered as he lets it go to the keeper once again.
Make that third leave in a row as Philander dishes out another ball outside off on a length.
FOUR! Crashed away! Short ball on middle, Denly rocks back and pulls it wide of the long on fence for a boundary.
Brilliant from Hamza at gully! A good length ball around off, Denly goes on the back foot and looks to run it down towards third man but Hamza dives to his right and saves runs for his side.

FOUR! Sprays down the leg side and gets the punishment. A ball on the pads on a good length, all Denly has to do is tickle it fine down the leg side. He does that nicely and the ball races to the fine leg fence. Rabada is leaking runs here. Not doing good to his partner who is bowling brilliantly at the other end.
Around off, tapped towards point.
Good length ball just outside off, Denly tucks it to point once again.
Outside off, left alone.
Good length ball around off, Stokes taps it towards the gully fielder.
Landed on off, Stokes comes forward and pushes it back to the bowler.
Fullish ball outside off, asking the left-hander to go for the drive. Stokes though is not interested as he makes a leave by covering his stumps.

Almost chopped on! A good length ball around off, Stokes defends it away from the body. The ball hits the lower part of the willow and balloons near the stumps. Stokes though is aware about it as he looks to keep the ball away. He does not need to do so as it does not go on the stumps anyway.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Uppish but safe! Fuller and outside off, Stokes drives away from the body. The ball takes the outer half of the bat and goes to point uppishly. A lot of oohs and aahs from the slip cordon.
Back of a length ball around off, Denly pulls but finds mid on.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Good length ball around off, Denly defends it towards cover off the back foot.
FOUR! Nicely done! A short ball outside off, Denly hangs back and guides it between the second slip and gully fielder. It races to the third man fence. Another boundary off Rabada.
Shortish around off, Denly works it behind square leg and takes a single.
Around off, it is defended.
Tossed up on off, Denly defends it off the front foot.
Flighted delivery on off, Denly plays it to point.
Full around off, Denly this time skips down the track and looks to go downtown over long on. However, the ball hits the lower part of the bat and goes to mid on who fumbles but no runs costed.
Outside off, it is left alone.
On off, Denly keeps it out.
FOUR! Over mid off! This time Denly reaches the pitch of this tossed up ball outside off and lofts it over mid off for a boundary. Looking really impressive ever since the first run he got.
Full and around off, pushed to mid off. The fielder there fumbles and allows Stokes to take a single and get off the mark.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Landed around off on a good length, Denly keeps it out.
Fuller and outside off, Denly blocks it off the front foot.
Flicked nicely! A good length ball on the pads, Denly whips it to mid-wicket. The mid on fielder chases it down and keeps the batters to a couple of runs.
In the channel outside off, it is left alone.
On a good length on off, Stokes looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Good length delivery on middle, Stokes offers a solid defense on this one.
On a good length on off, Stokes plays it back to the bowler.
Good length delivery on middle, Stokes pushes it through mid on. The batsmen get two runs.
FOUR! That is put away! Short delivery on middle, Stokes pulls it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
On a good length on off, Ben blocks it off the front foot.
Around off on a length, Denly blocks it out.
Fuller ball around off, pushed to cover.
Good length ball angled into the batter, Denly does well to keep it out.
Landed on middle, Denly flicks it between mid on and mid-wicket and takes a single.
On a good length on middle, Stokes defends it off the back foot.
Bowls it down the leg side, Stokes looks to flick but misses it.

Brilliant from Maharaj at gully. A full ball outside off, Denly drills the drive nicely but Maharaj dives full length to his right to make a half stop. The ball rolls just away and before he can get up and get to the ball, the batters cross.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
FOUR! Whipped nicely! Full delivery on middle, Stokes drives it through mid on for a boundary. 100 up for England.
Length delivery on off, Stokes taps it to point.
On a good length on off, Ben blocks it off the back foot.
On a length on middle, Stokes tucks it to mid-wicket.
On a length on middle, Denly nudges it towards the leg side.
Length delivery on off, Denly taps it towards point and takes a single.
On a length on middle, Stokes flicks it through mid-wicket. The batsmen cross ends.
Good length delivery on off, Denly blocks it off the front foot.
Bowls a bouncer, Denly does well to duck under it.
FOUR BYES! Bowls a bumper, Denly ducks under it. It goes towards Quinton de Kock who jumps and tries to stop by leaping but he can only get a glove on it. It ends up going to the third man fence.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Stokes blocks it off the back foot.
Floated delivery on off, Stokes  blocks it well.
Flighted delivery on middle, Stokes defends it out.
SIX! Don't bother looking that was six the moment it left the bat. Flighted on off, Stokes gets down on one knee and smashes it over the mid-wicket fence for a big six.

SIX! Two in a row. This one is a flat hit but once again hardly hit. Floated on off, Stokes once again gets down on one knee and slogs it flat over the mid-wicket fence for a maximum. 50-run stand is up between Ben Stokes and Joe Denly.
Restores calmness and defends it off the front foot.
Outside off, Denly offers no shot to this one.
On a good length on off, Denly defends it off the back foot.
FIVE WIDES! Bowls a bouncer down the leg side, Denly does well to duck under it. It goes way past the keeper towards fine leg for a boundary.
Good length delivery on off, Denly keeps it out.
Outside off, Joe leaves it alone.
Length delivery on middle, Denly flicks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
On a good length on off, Stokes defends it off the back foot.

Mix up but safe. The throw is at the wrong end. A shortish ball around off, Denly taps it towards point. There is a bit of confusion in the mind of Denly but seeing Stokes rushing at the other end, Denly too takes off. The throw comes at the striker's end but Stokes was quick to reach his crease. De Kock throws the ball back to the bowler at the non-striker's end but by the time it reaches, Denly is home.
Tossed up ball on middle, it is defended off the front foot.
Full delivery on off, Stokes drives it back towards the bowler.
Loopy delivery on middle, Stokes flicks it through square leg for a single.
Full delivery on middle, Denly drives it to mid on.
Flighted delivery on off, Denly punches it to point.
FOUR! Effortless from Stokes! Fullish ball on off, Stokes punches it beautifully. It reaches to the long on fence quickly. Sweet timing.
Around off, it is defended.
FOUR! Improvisation at its best. Short and outside off, Stokes goes on the back foot and at the very last moment guides it over the slip cordon. One bounce and into the fence.
Good length ball around off, pushed to point.
On middle, Stokes tucks it towards mid-wicket for a run.
Good length ball angled into the right-hander, Denly works it towards fine leg for a single.
Fuller and off, pushed to mid off.
